**Preservation rationale** (per EPIC #4960, Volet B étape 1):
- The upstream Vertues taxonomy complements the Fallacies taxonomy
  (sister CSV living in the same `Cards/Fallacies/` directory upstream).
  While the Fallacies taxonomy catalogs rhetorical defects (1,408 cards),
  the Vertues taxonomy catalogs rhetorical virtues (222 cards) — together
  they underpin Argumentum's bidirectional argumentation card dataset.
- CoursIA had previously NOT vendored this CSV at all — the data file
  was entirely absent from the `data/` directory, leaving the Vertues
  half of the Argumentum dataset undocumented in CoursIA notebooks.
- Importing verbatim is the "PAS de doublon" approach mandated by
  EPIC #4960 Volet B (verbatim upstream copy, no CoursIA regeneration).

Schema note — Vertues vs Fallacies
----------------------------------

The Vertues CSV schema is **deliberately different** from the Fallacies
CSV schema (both upstream, pinned at ac33f607):

| Aspect | Fallacies | Vertues |
|--------|-----------|---------|
| Header naming | mixed (PascalCase `Family_en` + snake_case `link_en`) | snake_case unified (`family_en`, `link_en`) |
| Card body fields | `text_/LTfr/Lfr115/example_fr/Lxfr145` (multi-field) | `title_/description_/remark_` (simplified 3-field) |
| Multilingual | 8 langs FR/EN/RU/PT/AR/ES/ZH/FA | same 8 langs |
| Cross-link columns | `crossLink_PredatesOn` ... `crossLink_IsRelatedTo` | same set |
| AIF columns | `AIF_skosDirectRef/ExceptionRef/Other/MappingType` | same set |
| Rows | 1,408 data rows (PK 0..1407) | 222 data rows (PK 0..222) |
| Columns | 106 | 78 |

Both schemas coexist upstream in the same directory (`Cards/Fallacies/`),
so consumers must NOT assume a unified schema across the two CSVs. This
is preserved verbatim in the CoursIA copies.

